        <heading>Section </heading>
        <content>
          <p>SECTION 5.  INVENTORY OF SUCCESSION PROPERTY
Art. 3131.  Notary appointed for inventory in each parish
When the court orders the taking of an inventory of the property of the succession, it shall appoint a notary of each parish in which the deceased left property to take the inventory of such property in that parish.</p>
        </content>
